description:
Story #1 - Archie - Smooch Me To Sleep - After his date with Veronica, Archie is looking forward to the goodnight kiss but Veronica refuses, saying she feel's a cold coming on and doesn't want him to catch it, to Archie not getting the kiss makes it seem like the date isn't complete and realizing he will never get to sleep without the kiss, he goes looking for a kiss and finds Betty who is happy to be his cure for insomnia.

Story #2 - Li'l Jinx - Pushy! - Jinx's friend Charley pushes her so she accuses him of taking advantage of a defenseless girl, after she beat's him up.

Story #3 - Archie - There's Alway's A Catch - While the school is being repainted Mr. Weatherbee moves the schools sports trophies to a safer place so they wouldn't get damaged, but as he moves the greatest trophy, the football from the school's first championship, he trip's and it flies out the window where Archie catches it and is so happy he spikes it and of course destroy's it.

Story #4 - Archie - Jest Quest - While recovering from a football injury, Archie has to stay out of school but he needs to study for his midterms so Mr. Weatherbee comes up with a solution, to use video tapes of the lessons but without all the sounds and things at school Archie can't concentrate so Betty and Jughead come up with a solution, a second tv and video tape of all the sounds of school, it works and Archie passes his test's.

Story #5 - Archie - The Bonnie Banks of Riverdale - Archie's great uncle sends him a set of bagpipes from Scotland but listening to Archie play them is torture for his parents and friends so Betty and Jughead give him a harmonica instead and while he can't play that either it's a lot better than bagpipes.

description:
Twist of Fate

Moose is on a rampage again, tying any boy who talks to his girlfriend Midge into knots! Can Mr. Weatherbee put a stop to this bad behavior?

Awesomely Awkward

The title says it all! Archie is a total klutz, but that might just save his life one day!

The Skin Game

Archie has taken to wearing a Davy Crocket-style raccoon skin cap. It's bound to make waves at school, but will it rub his fellow classmates the wrong way?

Write Stuff

George Gladir, one of Archie Comics' greatest writers, is having some trouble coming up with his latest story! Maybe his muse will help him bust the writer's block...

Finder's Fee

Archie, Betty and Veronica have come across a lost bracelet, and it's pretty valuable! Can they find the owner?

Tomato Surprise

No matter how hard he tries, Mr. Andrews simply can't get his tomatoes to grow. Can Archie help his poor father in the garden? n>

Cake Walk

Archie is helping move cakes down to the school bake sale! Unfortunately for Mr. Weatherbee, that means Archie has to carry them, and he knows how clumsy Archie can be! Mr. Svenson had better get ready to clean something up...

Chills and Thrills

The Polar Bear Club is a group of (crazy) people who go swimming in the middle of winter! Archie and Jughead are curious what the fuss is all about, so they agree to take the plunge. Is there any way this story doesn't end in hypothermia? Read on and see!

Biker Bungle

Betty and Veronica are enthralled when the gang gets some roadside assistance from a biker gang! Not to be outdone, Archie and Reggie are about to start wearing a lot more leather...
